(12) violates any rule made under this Act, for breach whereof a penalty may be incurred,
Panalty. shall be liable, on conviction before a Magistrate of such class as the l[Provincial
Government] directs 2in this behalf, to a fine not exceeding fifty rupees, or to imprisonment not
exceeding one month, or to both.
